This paper deals with machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural models for translation also suggests that it could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses tokenization and sub-word modeling, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language generation (cs.NE).
